{"title_page": "Gettysburg Union order of battle", "text_new": "{{Distinguish|Gettysburg Confederate order of battle{{!}}Confederate order of battle during the Battle of Gettysburg}}\nThe '''Union order of battle during the [[Battle of Gettysburg]]''' includes the [[American Civil War]] officers and men of the [[Army of the Potomac]] (multiple commander names indicate succession of command during the three-day battle (July 1&ndash;3, 1863)).\nOrder of battle compiled from the army organization during the battle,<ref>''Official Records, Series I, Volume XXVII, Part 1, [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0043&node=waro0043%3A2&view=image&seq=175&size=100 pages 155-168]; [http://www.nps.gov/gett/historyculture/aop-orderofbattle.htm Gettysburg National Military Park-Army of the Potomac] ''</ref> the casualty returns<ref>''Official Records, Series I, Volume XXVII, Part 1, [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0043&q1=return+of+casualties&view=image&seq=193&size=100 pages 173-187]''</ref> and the reports.<ref>''Official Records, Series I, Volume XXVII, Part 1, [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar;cc=moawar;q1=return%20of%20casualties;rgn=full%20text;idno=waro0043;didno=waro0043;view=image;seq=0025 pages 5-14] ''</ref>\n\n==Abbreviations used==\n\n===Military rank===\n* '''MG''' = [[Major General (United States)|Major General]]\n* '''BG''' = [[Brigadier General (United States)|Brigadier General]]\n* '''Col''' = [[Colonel (United States)|Colonel]]\n* '''Ltc''' = [[Lieutenant colonel (United States)|Lieutenant Colonel]]\n* '''Maj''' = [[Major (United States)|Major]]\n* '''Cpt''' = [[Captain (United States O-3)|Captain]]\n* '''Lt''' = [[1st Lieutenant#U.S. Army.2C U.S. Marine Corps and U.S. Air Force|Lieutenant]]\n* '''Sgt''' = [[Sergeant#American Civil War|Sergeant]]\n\n===Other===\n* '''w''' = [[Wounded in action|wounded]]\n* '''mw''' = mortally wounded \n* '''k''' = [[Killed in action|killed]]\n* '''c''' = [[Prisoner of war|captured]]\n* '''m''' = [[Missing in action|missing]]\n\n==[[Army of the Potomac]]==\nMG [[George G. Meade]], Commanding\n\n===General Staff and Headquarters===\n<br />\n'''General Staff''':\n* Chief of Staff: MG [[Daniel Butterfield]] ('''w''')\n* Assistant Adjutant General: BG [[Seth Williams]]\n* Assistant Inspector General: Col Edmund Schriver\n* Chief Quartermaster: BG [[Rufus Ingalls]]\n* Commissaries and subsistence: Col Henry F. Clarke\n* Chief of Artillery: BG [[Henry J. Hunt]] ('''w''')\n* Chief Ordnance Officer: Cpt [[Daniel Webster Flagler|Daniel W. Flagler]]\n* Chief Signal Officer: Cpt Lemuel B. Norton\n* Medical Director: Maj [[Jonathan Letterman]]\n* Chief of Engineers: BG [[Gouverneur K. Warren]] ('''w''')\n* Bureau of Military Information: Col [[George H. Sharpe]]\n<br />\n'''General Headquarters''':\n<br />\nCommand of the Provost Marshal General: BG [[Marsena R. Patrick]] <ref>[[93rd New York Volunteer Infantry|93rd New York]] and [[8th Infantry Regiment (United States)|8th United States]] not engaged</ref>\n* [[93rd New York Volunteer Infantry|93rd New York]]: Col John S. Crocker\n* [[8th Infantry Regiment (United States)|8th United States]] (8 companies): Cpt Edwin W. H. Read\n* [[2nd Pennsylvania Cavalry]]: Col Richard Butler Price\n* [[6th Pennsylvania Cavalry]] (Companies E & I): Cpt James Starr\n* Regular cavalry<ref>detachments from 1st, 2nd, 5th, and 6th Regiments</ref>\n\n<br />\nGuards and Orderlies:\n* Oneida (New York) Cavalry: Cpt Daniel P. Mann\n<br />\nEngineer Brigade: BG [[Henry W. Benham]] <ref>not engaged. With the exception of the regular battalion, it was July 1, and while at Beaver Dam Creek (Maryland), ordered to Washington D.C. , where it arrived July 3.</ref>\n* 15th New York (3 companies): Maj Walter L. Cassin\n* 50th New York: Col William H. Pettes\n* [[1st Engineer Battalion (United States)|U.S. Battalion]]: Cpt George H. Mendell\n\n===[[I Corps (Union Army)|I Corps]]===\nMG [[John F. Reynolds]] ('''k''')  <ref>Major General Reynolds, was killed July 1, while in command of the left wing of the army (I, III, and XI Corps and First Division, Cavalry Corps)</ref>\n<br>\nMG [[Abner Doubleday]] <ref>Major General Doubleday commanded the Corps July 1, and Major General Newton, who was assigned to that command on the 1st [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0045&node=waro0045%3A5&frm=frameset&view=image&seq=467] [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0107&node=waro0107%3A6&view=image&seq=1076&size=100], superseded him July 2</ref>\n<br>\nMG [[John Newton (engineer)|John Newton]]\n<br>\nGeneral Headquarters: \n* [[1st Maine Volunteer Cavalry Regiment|1st Maine Cavalry]], Company L: Cpt Constantine Taylor\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Division\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Brigade\n! Regiments and Others\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |\nFirst Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[James S. Wadsworth]][[File:Icorpsbadge1.png]]\n|\n| [[Iron Brigade|1st Brigade]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Solomon Meredith]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol William W. Robinson\n|\n* [[19th Indiana Volunteer Infantry Regiment|19th Indiana]]: Col Samuel J. Williams ('''w'''), Ltc [[William Wade Dudley|William W. Dudley]] ('''w'''), Maj John M. Lindley ('''w''')\n* [[24th Michigan]]: Col Henry A. Morrow ('''w&c'''), Ltc Mark Flanigan ('''w'''), Maj Edwin B. Wight ('''w'''), Cpt Albert M. Edwards\n* [[2nd Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|2nd Wisconsin]]: Col [[Lucius Fairchild]] ('''w&c'''), Ltc George H. Stevens ('''mw'''), Maj [[John Mansfield]] ('''w'''), Cpt George H. Otis\n* [[6th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|6th Wisconsin]]: Ltc [[Rufus Dawes]], Maj John F. Hauser\n* [[7th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|7th Wisconsin]]: Col William W. Robinson, Ltc John B. Callis ('''w&c'''), Maj Mark Finnicum ('''w''')\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Lysander Cutler]]\n|\n* [[7th Indiana Infantry Regiment|7th Indiana]]: Col Ira G. Grover\n* [[76th New York Volunteer Infantry|76th New York]]: Maj Andrew J. Grover ('''k''', July 1), Cpt John E. Cook ('''w''')\n* [[14th Regiment (New York State Militia)|84th New York]] (14th Militia): Col [[Edward Brush Fowler|Edward B. Fowler]] '''(w)''' Ltc R. B. Jordan '''(w)'''\n* [[95th New York Volunteer Infantry|95th New York]]: Col George H. Biddle ('''w''', July 1), Maj Edward Pye\n* [[147th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|147th New York]]: Ltc Francis C. Miller ('''w'''), Maj George Harney\n* [[56th Pennsylvania Infantry|56th Pennsylvania]] (9 companies): Col John William Hofmann\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |\nSecond Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[John C. Robinson]]|[[File:Icorpsbadge2.png]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Gabriel Rene Paul|Gabriel R. Paul]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Samuel H. Leonard ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Adrian R. Root]] ('''w&c''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Richard Coulter (general)|Richard Coulter]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Peter Lyle\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Richard Coulter\n|\n* [[16th Maine Volunteer Infantry Regiment|16th Maine]]: Col Charles W. Tilden ('''c'''), Cpt Daniel Marston\n* [[13th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|13th Massachusetts]]: Col Samuel H. Leonard, Ltc Nathaniel W. Batchelder\n* [[94th New York Volunteer Infantry|94th New York]]: Col [[Adrian R. Root]] ('''w/c''', July 1), Maj Samuel A. Moffett\n* [[104th New York Volunteer Infantry|104th New York]]: Col Gilbert G. Prey, Ltc Henry Tuthill ('''w''')\n* [[107th Pennsylvania Infantry|107th Pennsylvania]]: Ltc James McThomson ('''w''', July 1), Cpt Emanuel D. Roath\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Henry Baxter]]\n|\n* [[12th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|12th Massachusetts]]: Col [[James L. Bates]] ('''w'''), Ltc David Allen, Jr.\n* [[83rd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|83rd New York (9th Militia)]]: Ltc Joseph A. Moesch\n* [[97th New York Volunteer Infantry|97th New York]]: Col Charles Wheelock ('''w & c''', July 1), Ltc John P. Spofford ('''c''') Maj Charles B. Northrup\n* [[11th Pennsylvania Infantry|11th Pennsylvania]]:<ref>transferred, in afternoon of July 1, to the First Brigade</ref> Col Richard Coulter, Cpt Benjamin F. Haines ('''w'''), Cpt John B. Overmyer\n* [[88th Pennsylvania Infantry|88th Pennsylvania]]: Maj Benezet F. Foust ('''w''', July 1), Cpt Edmund A. Mass ('''c'''), Cpt Henry Whiteside\n* [[90th Pennsylvania Volunteer Infantry|90th Pennsylvania]]: Col Peter Lyle,<ref>temporarily transferred to the First Brigade</ref> Maj Alfred J. Sellers\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |\nThird Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMG [[Abner Doubleday]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Thomas A. Rowley]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMG Abner Doubleday[[File:Icorpsbadge3.png]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Chapman Biddle]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG Thomas A. Rowley ('''w''')\n|\n* [[80th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|80th New York (20th Militia)]]: Col Theodore B. Gates, Maj Walter A. Van Rensselaer ('''w''')\n* [[121st Pennsylvania Infantry|121st Pennsylvania]]: Col Chapman Biddle, Maj [[Alexander Biddle]]\n* [[142nd Pennsylvania Infantry|142nd Pennsylvania]]: Col Robert P. Cummins ('''mw'''), Ltc Alfred B. McCalmont, Maj Horatio N. Warren\n* [[151st Pennsylvania Infantry|151st Pennsylvania]]: Ltc [[George F. McFarland]] ('''w'''), Cpt Walter L. Owens, Col Harrison Allen\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Roy Stone]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Langhorne Wister]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Edmund L. Dana\n|\n* [[143rd Pennsylvania Infantry|143rd Pennsylvania]]: Col Edmund L. Dana, Ltc John D. Musser ('''w''')\n* [[149th Pennsylvania Infantry|149th Pennsylvania]]: Ltc Walton Dwight ('''w'''), Cpt James Glenn\n* [[150th Pennsylvania Infantry|150th Pennsylvania]]: Col