ion and not engaged in the Battle</ref>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt [[John C. Tidball]]\n|\n* 1st United States, Batteries [[1st U.S. Artillery, Battery E|E]] and [[1st U.S. Artillery, Battery G|G]]: Cpt [[Alanson Merwin Randol|Alanson M. Randol]]\n* [[1st U.S. Artillery, Battery K|1st United States, Battery K]]: Cpt [[William Montrose Graham, Jr.|William M. Graham, Jr.]]\n* [[2nd U.S. Artillery, Battery A|2nd United States, Battery A]]: Lt [[John Haskell Calef|John H. Calef]]\n|}\n\n===Artillery Reserve===\nBG [[Robert O. Tyler]]\n<br>\nCpt James M. Robertson\n\nHeadquarter Guard:\n* 32nd Massachusetts Infantry, Company C: Cpt Josiah C. Fuller\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:30%;\"|Brigade\n! Batteries\n|-\n| 1st Regular Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt [[Dunbar R. Ransom]] ('''w''')\n|\n* 1st United States, Battery H: Lt Chandler P. Eakin ('''w'''), Lt Philip D. Mason\n* 3rd United States, Batteries F and K: Lt John G. Turnbull\n* [[4th U.S. Artillery, Battery C|4th United States, Battery C]]: Lt Evan Thomas\n* [[5th U.S. Artillery, Battery C|5th United States, Battery C]]: Lt Gulian V. Weir ('''w''')\n|-\n| 1st Volunteer Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nLtc [[Freeman McGilvery]]\n|\n* Massachusetts Light, 5th Battery (E): Cpt Charles A. Phillips <ref>10th New York Battery attached</ref>\n* [[9th Massachusetts Light Artillery|Massachusetts Light, 9th Battery]]: Cpt John Bigelow ('''w'''), Lt Richard S. Milton\n* New York Light, 15th Battery: Cpt Patrick Hart ('''w'''), Lt Andrew R. McMahon\n* [[Independent Battery C, Pennsylvania Light Artillery|Pennsylvania Light, Battery C]] and [[Independent Battery F, Pennsylvania Light Artillery|Battery F]]: Cpt James Thompson ('''w''')\n|-\n| 2nd Volunteer Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt [[Elijah D. Taft]]\n|\n* [[1st Connecticut Heavy Artillery|1st Connecticut Heavy]], Battery B: Cpt Albert F. Brooker <ref name=not>not engaged</ref>\n* 1st Connecticut Heavy, Battery M: Cpt Franklin A. Pratt <ref name=not/>\n* Connecticut Light, 2nd Battery: Cpt John W. Sterling\n* [[5th New York Independent Light Artillery|New York Light, 5th Battery]]: Cpt Elijah D. Taft\n|-\n| 3rd Volunteer Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt James F. Huntington\n|\n* [[1st New Hampshire Light Battery|New Hampshire Light, 1st Battery]]: Cpt Frederick M. Edgell\n* [[Battery H, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery H]]: Lt George W. Norton\n* 1st Pennsylvania Light, [[Battery F, 1st Pennsylvania Light Artillery|Batteries F]] and G: Cpt [[R. Bruce Ricketts]]\n* West Virginia Light, Battery C: Cpt Wallace Hill\n|-\n| 4th Volunteer Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt Robert H. Fitzhugh\n|\n* [[6th Maine Battery|Maine Light, 6th Battery (F)]]: Lt Edwin B. Dow\n* [[Battery A, Maryland Light Artillery|Maryland Light, Battery A]]: Cpt James H. Rigby\n* [[Battery A, 1st Battery New Jersey Light Artillery|New Jersey Light, 1st Battery]]: Lt Augustine N. Parsons\n* [[Battery G, 1st New York Light Artillery|1st New York Light, Battery G]]: Cpt Nelson Ames\n* 1st New York Light, Battery K: Cpt Robert H. Fitzhugh <ref>[[11th New York Light Artillery|11th New York Battery]] attached</ref>\n|-\n| Train Guard\n|\n* [[4th New Jersey Volunteer Infantry|4th New Jersey Infantry]] (7 companies): Maj Charles Ewing\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==References==\n\n* U.S. War Department, [http://cdl.library.cornell.edu/moa/browse.monographs/waro.html ''The War of the Rebellion'']: ''a Compilation of the [[Official Records of the American Civil War|Official Records]] of the Union and Confederate Armies''. Washington, DC: U.S. Government Printing Office, 1880&ndash;1901.\n* [http://www.nps.gov/gett/historyculture/aop-orderofbattle.htm Gettysburg National Military Park - The Army of the Potomac at Gettysburg]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110603055742/http://www.civilwar.org/battlefields/gettysburg/gettysburg-history-articles/order-of-battle-aop-gettysburg.html Civil War Trust - Gettysburg Union order of battle]\n* [http://www.civilwarhome.com/gettysburgorderofbattle%28union%29.htm Civilwarhome - Gettysburg Union order of battle]\n* [http://www.gdg.org/research/OOB/Union/gburg_un.html Gettysburg Discussion Group - Union order of battle]\n* Eicher, John H. [http://www.gdg.org/Research/OOB/EicherOOB.htm \"Gettysburg Order of Battle\"] at Gettysburg Discussion Group website.\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Battle of Gettysburg}}\n\n{{Battle of Gettysburg}}\n\n[[Category:American Civil War orders of battle]]\n[[Category:Battle of Gettysburg|*]]\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|Gettysburg Confederate order of battle{{!}}Confederate order of battle during the Battle of Gettysburg}}\nThe '''Union order of battle during the [[Battle of Gettysburg]]''' includes the [[American Civil War]] officers and men of the [[Army of the Potomac]] (multiple commander names indicate succession of command during the three-day battle (July 1&ndash;3, 1863)).\nOrder of battle compiled from the army organization during the battle,<ref>''Official Records, Series I, Volume XXVII, Part 1, [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0043&node=waro0043%3A2&view=image&seq=175&size=100 pages 155-168]; [http://www.nps.gov/gett/historyculture/aop-orderofbattle.htm Gettysburg National Military Park-Army of the Potomac] ''</ref> the casualty returns<ref>''Official Records, Series I, Volume XXVII, Part 1, [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0043&q1=return+of+casualties&view=image&seq=193&size=100 pages 173-187]''</ref> and the reports.<ref>''Official Records, Series I, Volume XXVII, Part 1, [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar;cc=moawar;q1=return%20of%20casualties;rgn=full%20text;idno=waro0043;didno=waro0043;view=image;seq=0025 pages 5-14] ''</ref>\n\n==Abbreviations used==\n\n===Military rank===\n* '''MG''' = [[Major General (United States)|Major General]]\n* '''BG''' = [[Brigadier General (United States)|Brigadier General]]\n* '''Col''' = [[Colonel (United States)|Colonel]]\n* '''Ltc''' = [[Lieutenant colonel (United States)|Lieutenant Colonel]]\n* '''Maj''' = [[Major (United States)|Major]]\n* '''Cpt''' = [[Captain (United States O-3)|Captain]]\n* '''Lt''' = [[1st Lieutenant#U.S. Army.2C U.S. Marine Corps and U.S. Air Force|Lieutenant]]\n* '''Sgt''' = [[Sergeant#American Civil War|Sergeant]]\n\n===Other===\n* '''w''' = [[Wounded in action|wounded]]\n* '''mw''' = mortally wounded \n* '''k''' = [[Killed in action|killed]]\n* '''c''' = [[Prisoner of war|captured]]\n* '''m''' = [[Missing in action|missing]]\n\n==[[Army of the Potomac]]==\nMG [[George G. Meade]], Commanding\n\n===General Staff and Headquarters===\n<br />\n'''General Staff''':\n* Chief of Staff: MG [[Daniel Butterfield]] ('''w''')\n* Assistant Adjutant General: BG [[Seth Williams]]\n* Assistant Inspector General: Col Edmund Schriver\n* Chief Quartermaster: BG [[Rufus Ingalls]]\n* Commissaries and subsistence: Col Henry F. Clarke\n* Chief of Artillery: BG [[Henry J. Hunt]] ('''w''')\n* Chief Ordnance Officer: Cpt [[Daniel Webster Flagler|Daniel W. Flagler]]\n* Chief Signal Officer: Cpt Lemuel B. Norton\n* Medical Director: Maj [[Jonathan Letterman]]\n* Chief of Engineers: BG [[Gouverneur K. Warren]] ('''w''')\n* Bureau of Military Information: Col [[George H. Sharpe]]\n<br />\n'''General Headquarters''':\n<br />\nCommand of the Provost Marshal General: BG [[Marsena R. Patrick]] <ref>[[93rd New York Volunteer Infantry|93rd New York]] and [[8th Infantry Regiment (United States)|8th United States]] not engaged</ref>\n* [[93rd New York Volunteer Infantry|93rd New York]]: Col John S. Crocker\n* [[8th Infantry Regiment (United States)|8th United States]] (8 companies): Cpt Edwin W. H. Read\n* [[2nd Pennsylvania Cavalry]]: Col Richard Butler Price\n* [[6th Pennsylvania Cavalry]] (Companies E & I): Cpt James Starr\n* Regular cavalry<ref>detachments from 1st, 2nd, 5th, and 6th Regiments</ref>\n\n<br />\nGuards and Orderlies:\n* Oneida (New York) Cavalry: Cpt Daniel P. Mann\n<br />\nEngineer Brigade: BG [[Henry W. Benham]] <ref>not engaged. With the exception of the regular battalion, it was July 1, and while at Beaver Dam Creek (Maryland), ordered to Washington D.C. , where it arrived July 3.</ref>\n* 15th New York (3 companies): Maj Walter L. Cassin\n* 50th New York: Col William H. Pettes\n* [[1st Engineer Battalion (United States)|U.S. Battalion]]: Cpt George H. Mendell\n\n===[[I Corps (Union Army)|I Corps]]===\nMG [[John F. Reynolds]] ('''k''')  <ref>Major General Reynolds, was killed July 1, while in command of the left wing of the army (I, III, and XI Corps and First Division, Cavalry Corps)</ref>\n<br>\nMG [[Abner Doubleday]] <ref>Major General Doubleday commanded the Corps July 1, and Major General Newton, who was assigned to that command on the 1st [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0045&node=waro0045%3A5&frm=frameset&view=image&seq=467] [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0107&node=waro0107%3A6&view=image&seq=1076&size=100], superseded him July 2</ref>\n<br>\nMG [[John Newton (engineer)|John Newton]]\n<br>\nGeneral Headquarters: \n* [[1st Maine Volunteer Cavalry Regiment|1st Maine Cavalry]], Company L: Cpt Constantine Taylor\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Division\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Brigade\n! Regiments and Others\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |\nFirst Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[James S. Wadsworth]][[File:Icorpsbadge1.png]]\n|\n| [[Iron Brigade|1st Brigade]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Solomon Meredith]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol William W. Robinson\n|\n* [[19th Indiana Volunteer Infantry Regiment|19th Indiana]]: Col Samuel J. Williams ('''w'''), Ltc [[William Wade Dudley|William W. Dudley]] ('''w'''), Maj John M. Lindley ('''w''')\n* [[24th Michigan]]: Col Henry A. Morrow ('''w&c'''), Ltc Mark Flanigan ('''w'''), Maj Edwin B. Wight ('''w'''), Cpt Albert M. Edwards\n* [[2nd Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|2nd Wisconsin]]: Col [[Lucius Fairchild]] ('''w&c'''), Ltc George H. Stevens ('''mw'''), Maj [[John Mansfield]] ('''w'''), Cpt George H. Otis\n* [[6th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|6th Wisconsin]]: Ltc [[Rufus Dawes]], Maj John F. Hauser\n* [[7th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|7th Wisconsin]]: Col William W. Robinson, Ltc John B. Callis ('''w&c'''), Maj Mark Finnicum ('''w''')\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Lysander Cutler]]\n|\n* [[7th Indiana Infantry Regiment|7th Indiana]]: Col Ira G. Grover\n* [[76th New York Volunteer Infantry|76th New York]]: Maj Andrew J. Grover ('''k''', July 1), Cpt John E. Cook ('''w''')\n* [[14th Regiment (New York State Militia)|84th New York]] (14th Militia): Col [[Edward Brush Fowler|Edward B. Fowler]] '''(w)''' Ltc R. B. Jordan '''(w)'''\n* [[95th New York Volunteer Infantry|95th New York]]: Col George H. Biddle ('''w''', July 1), Maj Edward Pye\n* [[147th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|147th New York]]: Ltc Francis C. Miller ('''w'''), Maj George Harney\n* [[56th Pennsylvania Infantry|56th Pennsylvania]] (9 companies): Col John William Hofmann\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |\nSecond Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[John C. Robinson]]|[[File:Icorpsbadge2.png]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Gabriel Rene Paul|Gabriel R. Paul]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Samuel H. Leonard ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Adrian R. Root]] ('''w&c''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Richard Coulter (general)|Richard Coulter]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Peter Lyle\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Richard Coulter\n|\n* [[16th Maine Volunteer Infantry Regiment|16th Maine]]: Col Charles W. Tilden ('''c'''), Cpt Daniel Marston\n* [[13th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|13th Massachusetts]]: Col Samuel H. Leonard, Ltc Nathaniel W. Batchelder\n* [[94th New York Volunteer Infantry|94th New York]]: Col [[Adrian R. Root]] ('''w/c''', July 1), Maj Samuel A. Moffett\n* [[104th New York Volunteer Infantry|104th New York]]: Col Gilbert G. Prey, Ltc Henry Tuthill ('''w''')\n* [[107th Pennsylvania Infantry|107th Pennsylvania]]: Ltc James McThomson ('''w''', July 1), Cpt Emanuel D. Roath\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Henry Baxter]]\n|\n* [[12th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|12th Massachusetts]]: Col [[James L. Bates]] ('''w'''), Ltc David Allen, Jr.\n* [[83rd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|83rd New York (9th Militia)]]: Ltc Joseph A. Moesch\n* [[97th New York Volunteer Infantry|97th New York]]: Col Charles Wheelock ('''w & c''', July 1), Ltc John P. Spofford ('''c''') Maj Charles B. Northrup\n* [[11th Pennsylvania Infantry|11th Pennsylvania]]:<ref>transferred, in afternoon of July 1, to the First Brigade</ref> Col Richard Coulter, Cpt Benjamin F. Haines ('''w'''), Cpt John B. Overmyer\n* [[88th Pennsylvania Infantry|88th Pennsylvania]]: Maj Benezet F. Foust ('''w''', July 1), Cpt Edmund A. Mass ('''c'''), Cpt Henry Whiteside\n* [[90th Pennsylvania Volunteer Infantry|90th Pennsylvania]]: Col Peter Lyle,<ref>temporarily transferred to the First Brigade</ref> Maj Alfred J. Sellers\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |\nThird Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMG [[Abner Doubleday]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Thomas A. Rowley]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMG Abner Doubleday[[File:Icorpsbadge1.png]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Chapman Biddle]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG Thomas A. Rowley ('''w''')\n|\n* [[80th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|80th New York (20th Militia)]]: Col Theodore B. Gates, Maj Walter A. Van Rensselaer ('''w''')\n* [[121st Pennsylvania Infantry|121st Pennsylvania]]: Col Chapman Biddle, Maj [[Alexander Biddle]]\n* [[142nd Pennsylvania Infantry|142nd Pennsylvania]]: Col Robert P. Cummins ('''mw'''), Ltc Alfred B. McCalmont, Maj Horatio N. Warren\n* [[151st Pennsylvania Infantry|151st Pennsylvania]]: Ltc [[George F. McFarland]] ('''w'''), Cpt Walter L. Owens, Col Harrison Allen\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Roy Stone]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Langhorne Wister]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Edmund L. Dana\n|\n* [[143rd Pennsylvania Infantry|143rd Pennsylvania]]: Col Edmund L. Dana, Ltc John D. Musser ('''w''')\n* [[149th Pennsylvania Infantry|149th Pennsylvania]]: Ltc Walton Dwight ('''w'''), Cpt James Glenn\n* [[150th Pennsylvania Infantry|150th Pennsylvania]]: Col Langhorne Wister, Ltc [[Henry S. Huidekoper]] ('''w'''), Maj Thomas Chamberlin ('''w'''), Cpt Cornelius C. Widdis ('''c'''), Cpt George W. Jones\n|-\n| [[2nd Vermont Brigade|3rd Brigade]] <ref>arrived on the evening of July 1 and did not take part on the first day of the battle [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0043&node=waro0043%3A8&frm=frameset&view=image&seq=368]; [[12th Vermont Infantry|12th Vermont]] and [[15th Vermont Infantry|15th Vermont]] were detached as train guard</ref>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[George J. Stannard]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Francis V. Randall\n|\n* [[13th Vermont Infantry|13th Vermont]]: Col Francis V. Randall, Ltc William D. Munson ('''w'''), Maj Joseph J. Boynton\n* [[14th Vermont Infantry|14th Vermont]]: Col [[William T. Nichols]], Ltc Charles W. Rose\n* [[16th Vermont Infantry|16th Vermont]]: Col [[Wheelock G. Veazey]], Maj William Rounds\n|-\n|\n| Artillery Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Charles S. Wainwright]]\n|\n* [[2nd Maine Battery|Maine Light, 2nd Battery (B)]]: Cpt James A. Hall\n* [[5th Maine Battery|Maine Light, 5th Battery (E)]]: Cpt [[Greenleaf T. Stevens]] ('''w'''), Lt Edward N. Whittier\n* 1st New York Light, Battery E & [[Battery L, 1st New York Light Artillery|Battery L]]: Cpt Gilbert H. Reynolds ('''w''', July 1), Lt George Breck\n* [[Battery B, 1st Pennsylvania Light Artillery|1st Pennsylvania Light, Battery B]]: Cpt James H. Cooper\n* [[4th U.S. Artillery, Battery B|4th United States, Battery B]]: Lt [[James Stewart (artilleryman)|James Stewart]] ('''w'''), Lt James Davison ('''w''')\n|}\n\n===[[II Corps (Union Army)|II Corps]]===\nMG [[Winfield S. Hancock]]<ref>After the death of General Reynolds, General Hancock was assigned to the command of all troops on the field of battle [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0045&node=waro0045%3A5&frm=frameset&view=image&seq=463], relieving General Howard, who had succeeded General Reynolds. General Gibbon, of the Second Division, assumed command of the corps. These assignments terminated on the evening of July 1. Similar changes in commanders occurred during the battle of the 2nd, when General Hancock was put in command of the Third Corps in addition to that of his own. He was wounded on the 3rd, and Brigadier General William Hays [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0045&node=waro0045%3A5&frm=frameset&view=image&seq=505] was assigned to the command of the corps.</ref> ('''w''')\n<br>\nBG [[John Gibbon]]\n<br>\nBG [[William Hays (general)|William Hays]]\n<br>\nGeneral Headquarters:\n* 6th New York Cavalry, Companies D and K: Cpt Riley Johnson (Escort)\n* [[53rd Pennsylvania Infantry]] , Companies A, B and K: Maj Octavus Bull (Provost Marshal 2nd Corps) <ref>under the command of General Patrick (Provost Marshal General of the Army) during the battle [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0043&node=waro0043%3A8&frm=frameset&view=image&seq=396]</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Division\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Brigade\n! Regiments and Others\n|-\n| rowspan=4 |\nFirst Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[John C. Caldwell]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Edward E. Cross]] ('''mw''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[H. Boyd McKeen]]\n|\n* [[5th New Hampshire Volunteer Infantry|5th New Hampshire]]: Ltc Charles E. Hapgood, Maj Richard E. Cross\n* [[61st New York Volunteer Infantry|61st New York]]: Ltc [[K. Oscar Broady]]\n* [[81st Pennsylvania Infantry|81st Pennsylvania]]: Col Henry Boyd McKeen, Ltc Amos Stroh\n* [[148th Pennsylvania Infantry|148th Pennsylvania]]: Col H. Boyd McKeen,<ref>Col McKeen was placed in temporary command of the 148th Pennsylvania Infantry because Colonel James Addams Beaver was ill. Col Edward E. Cross believed that Ltc McFarlane was too inexperienced to lead the regiment.</ref> Ltc Robert McFarlane, Maj Robert H. Foster\n|-\n| [[Irish Brigade (US)|2nd Brigade]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Patrick Kelly (Colonel)|Patrick Kelly]]\n|\n* [[28th Massachusetts Infantry regiment|28th Massachusetts]]: Col Richard Byrnes\n* [[63rd New York Infantry]] (2 companies): Ltc Richard C. Bentley ('''w'''), Cpt Thomas Touhy\n* [[U.S. 69th Infantry Regiment|69th New York]] (2 companies): Cpt Richard Moroney ('''w'''), Lt James J. Smith\n* [[88th New York Infantry]] (2 companies): Cpt Denis F. Burke\n* [[116th Pennsylvania Infantry|116th Pennsylvania]] (4 companies): Maj [[St. Clair Augustine Mulholland|St. Clair A. Mulholland]]\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Samuel K. Zook]] ('''mw''' July 2)\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nLtc Charles G. Freudenberg ('''w''' July 2)\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Richard P. Roberts ('''k''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nLtc John Fraser\n|\n* [[52nd New York Volunteer Infantry|52nd New York]]: Ltc Charles G. Freudenberg ('''w''' July 2), Maj Edward Venuti ('''k'''), Cpt William Scherrer\n* [[57th New York Volunteer Infantry|57th New York]]: Ltc Alford B. Chapman\n* [[66th New York Volunteer Infantry|66th New York]]: Col Orlando H. Morris ('''w'''), Ltc John S. Hammell ('''w'''), Maj Peter A. Nelson\n* [[140th Pennsylvania Volunteer Infantry|140th Pennsylvania]]: Col Richard P. Roberts, Ltc John Fraser, Maj Thomas Rodgers\n|-\n| 4th Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[John R. Brooke]] ('''w''')\n|\n* [[27th Connecticut Infantry Regiment|27th Connecticut]] 