illiam Gamble (general)|William Gamble]]\n|\n* [[8th Regiment Illinois Volunteer Cavalry|8th Illinois Cavalry]]: Maj [[John Lourie Beveridge|John L. Beveridge]]\n* [[12th Illinois Cavalry]] (4 companies) and 3rd Indiana Cavalry (6 companies): Col [[George H. Chapman]], Maj Charles Lemmon ('''mw''')\n* 8th New York Cavalry: Ltc William L. Markell\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Thomas Devin]]\n|\n* 6th New York Cavalry (6 companies): Maj William E. Beardsley\n* [[9th Regiment New York Volunteer Cavalry|9th New York Cavalry]]: Col William Sackett\n* [[17th Pennsylvania Cavalry]]: Col Josiah H. Kellogg\n* [[3rd West Virginia Volunteer Cavalry Regiment|3rd West Virginia Cavalry]], Companies A and C: Cpt Seymour B. Conger\n|-\n| Reserve Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Wesley Merritt]]\n|\n* [[6th Pennsylvania Cavalry]]: Maj James H. Haseltine\n* [[U.S. 1st Cavalry Regiment|1st United States Cavalry]]: Cpt Richard S. C. Lord\n* [[U.S. 2d Cavalry Regiment|2nd United States Cavalry]]: Cpt [[Theophilus Francis Rodenbough|Theophilus F. Rodenbough]]\n* [[U.S. 5th Cavalry Regiment|5th United States Cavalry]]: Cpt Julius W. Mason\n* [[U.S. 6th Cavalry Regiment|6th United States Cavalry]]: Maj [[Samuel H. Starr]] ('''w'''), Lt [[Louis H. Carpenter]], Lt [[Nicholas M. Nolan]], Cpt [[Ira W. Claflin]] ('''w''')\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |\nSecond Division <ref>The Second Brigade (2nd and 4th New York Cavalry, [[6th Ohio Cavalry]], and [[8th Pennsylvania Cavalry]]) under Colonel [[Pennock Huey]] was at Westminster, and not engaged in the battle</ref>\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[David McMurtrie Gregg]]\n|  1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[John Baillie McIntosh|John B. McIntosh]]\n|\n* [[1st Regiment Maryland Volunteer Cavalry|1st Maryland Cavalry]] (11 companies): Ltc James M. Deems\n* Purnell (Maryland) Cavalry Legion, Company A: Cpt Robert E. Duvall\n* [[1st Massachusetts Volunteer Cavalry|1st Massachusetts Cavalry]]: Ltc [[Greely S. Curtis]]<ref>Served with VI Corps, and on the right flank.</ref>\n* [[1st New Jersey Volunteer Cavalry|1st New Jersey Cavalry]]: Maj Myron H. Beaumont\n* [[1st Pennsylvania Cavalry]]: Col John P. Taylor\n* [[3rd Pennsylvania Cavalry]]: Ltc Edward S. Jones\n* [[3rd Pennsylvania Heavy Artillery]], Section, Battery H: Cpt William D. Rank<ref>Served as light artillery.</ref>\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[John Irvin Gregg]]\n|\n* [[1st Maine Volunteer Cavalry Regiment|1st Maine Cavalry]] (10 companies): Ltc Charles H. Smith\n* [[10th New York Cavalry]]: Maj Mathew Henry Avery\n* [[4th Pennsylvania Cavalry]]: Ltc William E. Doster\n* [[16th Pennsylvania Cavalry]]: Ltc John K. Robison\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |\nThird Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Judson Kilpatrick]]\n|  1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Elon J. Farnsworth]] ('''k''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Nathaniel P. Richmond\n|\n* [[5th Regiment New York Volunteer Cavalry|5th New York Cavalry]]: Maj [[John Hammond (U.S. Representative)|John Hammond]]\n* 18th Pennsylvania Cavalry: Ltc William P. Brinton\n* [[1st Vermont Cavalry]]: Col Addison W. Preston\n* [[1st West Virginia Volunteer Cavalry Regiment|1st West Virginia Cavalry]] (10 companies): Col Nathaniel P. Richmond, Maj [[Charles E. Capehart]]\n|-\n|[[Michigan Brigade|2nd Brigade]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[George A. Custer]]\n|\n* [[1st Michigan Volunteer Cavalry Regiment|1st Michigan Cavalry]]: Col Charles H. Town, Ltc Peter Stagg ('''w''')\n* [[5th Michigan Volunteer Cavalry Regiment|5th Michigan Cavalry]]: Col [[Russell A. Alger]], Ltc Ebenezer Gould ('''w'''), Maj Noah H. Ferry ('''k''')\n* [[6th Michigan Volunteer Cavalry Regiment|6th Michigan Cavalry]]: Col George Gray\n* [[7th Michigan Volunteer Cavalry Regiment|7th Michigan Cavalry]]: (10 companies): Col [[William D. Mann]]\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |\n[[U.S. Horse Artillery Brigade|Horse Artillery]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt [[James Madison Robertson|James M. Robertson]]\n|\n* [[Battery \"I\" 1st Regiment Michigan Light Artillery|9th Michigan Battery]]: Cpt Jabez J. Daniels\n* 6th New York Battery: Cpt Joseph W. Martin\n* 2nd United States, Batteries B and L: Lt Edward Heaton\n* 2nd United States, Battery M: Lt [[Alexander Cummings McWhorter Pennington, Jr.|Alexander C. M. Pennington, Jr.]]\n* [[4th U.S. Artillery, Battery E|4th United States, Battery E]]: Lt [[Samuel Sherer Elder|Samuel S. Elder]]\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade <ref>Battery C, 3rd United States was with the Second Brigade, Second Division and not engaged in the Battle</ref>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt [[John C. Tidball]]\n|\n* 1st United States, Batteries [[1st U.S. Artillery, Battery E|E]] and [[1st U.S. Artillery, Battery G|G]]: Cpt [[Alanson Merwin Randol|Alanson M. Randol]]\n* [[1st U.S. Artillery, Battery K|1st United States, Battery K]]: Cpt [[William Montrose Graham, Jr.|William M. Graham, Jr.]]\n* [[2nd U.S. Artillery, Battery A|2nd United States, Battery A]]: Lt [[John Haskell Calef|John H. Calef]]\n|}\n\n===Artillery Reserve===\nBG [[Robert O. Tyler]]\n<br>\nCpt James M. Robertson\n\nHeadquarter Guard:\n* 32nd Massachusetts Infantry, Company C: Cpt Josiah C. Fuller\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:30%;\"|Brigade\n! Batteries\n|-\n| 1st Regular Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt [[Dunbar R. Ransom]] ('''w''')\n|\n* 1st United States, Battery H: Lt Chandler P. Eakin ('''w'''), Lt Philip D. Mason\n* 3rd United States, Batteries F and K: Lt John G. Turnbull\n* [[4th U.S. Artillery, Battery C|4th United States, Battery C]]: Lt Evan Thomas\n* [[5th U.S. Artillery, Battery C|5th United States, Battery C]]: Lt Gulian V. Weir ('''w''')\n|-\n| 1st Volunteer Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nLtc [[Freeman McGilvery]]\n|\n* Massachusetts Light, 5th Battery (E): Cpt Charles A. Phillips <ref>10th New York Battery attached</ref>\n* [[9th Massachusetts Light Artillery|Massachusetts Light, 9th Battery]]: Cpt John Bigelow ('''w'''), Lt Richard S. Milton\n* New York Light, 15th Battery: Cpt Patrick Hart ('''w'''), Lt Andrew R. McMahon\n* [[Independent Battery C, Pennsylvania Light Artillery|Pennsylvania Light, Battery C]] and [[Independent Battery F, Pennsylvania Light Artillery|Battery F]]: Cpt James Thompson ('''w''')\n|-\n| 2nd Volunteer Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt [[Elijah D. Taft]]\n|\n* [[1st Connecticut Heavy Artillery|1st Connecticut Heavy]], Battery B: Cpt Albert F. Brooker <ref name=not>not engaged</ref>\n* 1st Connecticut Heavy, Battery M: Cpt Franklin A. Pratt <ref name=not/>\n* Connecticut Light, 2nd Battery: Cpt John W. Sterling\n* [[5th New York Independent Light Artillery|New York Light, 5th Battery]]: Cpt Elijah D. Taft\n|-\n| 3rd Volunteer Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt James F. Huntington\n|\n* [[1st New Hampshire Light Battery|New Hampshire Light, 1st Battery]]: Cpt Frederick M. Edgell\n* [[Battery H, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery H]]: Lt George W. Norton\n* 1st Pennsylvania Light, [[Battery F, 1st Pennsylvania Light Artillery|Batteries F]] and G: Cpt [[R. Bruce Ricketts]]\n* West Virginia Light, Battery C: Cpt Wallace Hill\n|-\n| 4th Volunteer Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt Robert H. Fitzhugh\n|\n* [[6th Maine Battery|Maine Light, 6th Battery (F)]]: Lt Edwin B. Dow\n* [[Battery A, Maryland Light Artillery|Maryland Light, Battery A]]: Cpt James H. Rigby\n* [[Battery A, 1st Battery New Jersey Light Artillery|New Jersey Light, 1st Battery]]: Lt Augustine N. Parsons\n* [[Battery G, 1st New York Light Artillery|1st New York Light, Battery G]]: Cpt Nelson Ames\n* 1st New York Light, Battery K: Cpt Robert H. Fitzhugh <ref>[[11th New York Light Artillery|11th New York Battery]] attached</ref>\n|-\n| Train Guard\n|\n* [[4th New Jersey Volunteer Infantry|4th New Jersey Infantry]] (7 companies): Maj Charles Ewing\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==References==\n\n* U.S. War Department, [http://cdl.library.cornell.edu/moa/browse.monographs/waro.html ''The War of the Rebellion'']: ''a Compilation of the [[Official Records of the American Civil